WEBVTT

00:02:29.458 --> 00:02:33.133
and then later, I transferred into
the Legal Aid Society in New York City.

00:02:33.157 --> 00:02:35.922
And I loved the work;
I loved everybody I was working with,

00:02:35.946 --> 00:02:37.864
I thought my colleagues were incredible,

00:02:37.888 --> 00:02:40.841
I thought the clients were inspiring
in the face of all odds,

00:02:40.865 --> 00:02:44.319
and I loved representing
people in courtrooms.

00:02:44.343 --> 00:02:48.058
But I also could always see the gaps
in what we were doing.

00:02:48.082 --> 00:02:51.840
I saw the disconnect between
the communities that clients came from

00:02:51.864 --> 00:02:53.788
and the people that were defending them.

00:02:53.812 --> 00:02:57.561
I saw the gaps in what kind
of representation we were providing.

00:02:57.585 --> 00:02:59.598
When clients would sit across the table

00:02:59.622 --> 00:03:01.829
and I would be focusing
on their criminal case,